cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with structured classification tasks in Natural Language Processing. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses online learning algorithms and their performance. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes alternatives to compute confidence in the output of non-probabilistic algorithms. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possibility as the paper discusses methods to detect mislabeled words, which could be relevant in image classification tasks. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possibility as the paper discusses active learning, which is a common technique in neural network training.
